value.0: A fine stringed instrument, a lute is very mobile, and as such, a favorite of traveling minstrels everywhere.  It has a pleasing sound, as the strings musical vibrations echo in the hollow wooden chamber and reverberate.
A harp is a stringed instrument, which often produces dulcet gentle tones, assuming the person playing it has any talent for such things, of course.
